Nasarawa State Police Command has rescued a former councillor in Calabar South Local Government Area of Cross River State, Mr Anthony Duke Effiom. In a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, ASP Ramhan Nansel and obtained by Daily Trust on Sunday, the police said that it recovered one AK 47 rifle with an empty magazine during the arrest. N788bn earned profit: Dangote, 4 other firms to watch this year Abba Kyari posts fresh wedding pictures amid backlash, says ‘my people love me’ The PPRO explained that on Tuesday, about 9:50 pm, the police received a distress call that yet-to-be-identified gunmen barricaded the road at Kurmin Shinkafa along Akwanga-Keffi expressway and abducted one, Mr Anthony Duke Effiom, a former councillor in Calabar South Local Government Area of Cross River state. According to him, “Upon receipt of the information, the Commissioner of Police, Mr Adesina Soyemi drafted the personnel of the command attached to Garaku Division, all the tactical teams of the Command in collaboration with operatives of the Inspector General of Police, Intelligence Response Team to go after the kidnappers. “Consequently, on Saturday at about 1 am, the operatives trailed the abductors to their hideout at Angwan Maigini Village, where the personnel engaged them in a gun battle. Succumbing to the superior firepower, the hoodlums escaped into the forest at various locations with varying degrees of injuries and the victim was rescued unhurt by the police,” the statement added. The Commissioner Police, Mr Soyemi commended the police operatives for a job well done and praised their pragmatic display of gallantry.